1
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:29,240
Still reading?

2
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:31,760
I've finished comparing them.

3
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:33,760
I got four multiple-choice questions wrong,

4
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:34,520
three fill-in-the-blank questions,

5
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:35,680
and one short answer question.

6
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,740
Hey, don't you need to go to tutoring?

7
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:43,200
Ah, I'm off.

8
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:49,000
Zixi, during the exam the other day,

9
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,840
you bought me time.

10
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:51,920
I

11
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:53,720
was very touched.

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:55,600
Boss.

13
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,520
Is what you're writing really useful?

14
00:00:58,920 --> 00:00:59,800
Hao.

15
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:01,920
When dealing with girls,

16
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:04,050
you must choose every word carefully.

17
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,000
Show-off.

18
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:11,440
Did you deliver the test answers?

19
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:12,360
Delivered.

20
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:14,050
Did she accept them?

21
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,039
I slid them under her door.

22
00:01:15,039 --> 00:01:16,240
She couldn't refuse.

23
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,440
She doesn't know I sent them.

24
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:21,370
Does she need to know you sent them?

25
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,420
Good thing.

26
00:01:25,039 --> 00:01:25,840
I left a mark.

27
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:29,000
You made that mark?

28
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,440
Erased it.

29
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,120
I don't think I erased it.

30
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,240
I didn't give you these answers.

31
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,800
I can tell.

32
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:53,640
The score for these answers is exactly 60, just enough to pass.

33
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:54,479
Really?

34
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,800
No wonder when I checked them last night,

35
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,360
I felt something was fishy.

36
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:00,720
Are you done?

37
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,640
I'm sick of doing this.

38
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:06,600
Tutoring requires a study plan tailored to your level.

39
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:09,000
Otherwise, it's twice the effort for half the result.

40
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,160
Glad you know.

41
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:15,840
I'm done.

42
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,079
So many mistakes.

43
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:37,920
Did you just start learning yesterday?

44
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,360
Not entirely.

45
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,300
I still have some ancient memory points.

46
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,280
What?

47
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,040
Everyone, back to your seats.

48
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,840
Quiet down and get ready for class.

49
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:50,360
Let's take roll first.

50
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,760
Why isn't Zixi in class?

51
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:52,320
Guo Long.

52
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:52,880
Here.

53
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,079
Yang Qian.

54
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:54,920
Here.

55
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:56,760
Mo Xiaoming.

56
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,560
Here.

57
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,600
Qiu Kexin.

58
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,040
Here.

59
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,360
Yin Zixi.

60
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:02,120
Here.

61
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,120
Yang Chunfeng.

62
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:04,720
Here.

63
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,800
Liang Chen.

64
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:09,880
Liang Chen.

65
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:10,920
Here.

66
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:13,720
Luo Zicong.

67
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,840
The beginning of this passage is to arouse readers' interest,

68
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:20,320
and convey facts in concise and clear language

69
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,250
at the same time.

70
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,440
Okay.

71
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:27,760
Next, five minutes to review the basic characteristics of news.

72
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,480
Senior,

73
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:31,040
shouldn't the next five minutes be a break?

74
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,640
Reviewing is resting.

75
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,600
What?

76
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:35,640
Twenty-five minutes of focused study,

77
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:36,640
and five minutes of review.

78
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,880
After two rounds,

79
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,640
there will be a 15-minute assessment.

80
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,920
This constitutes one study cycle.

81
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:43,380
Complete 20 cycles today to meet the target.

82
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,200
Hurry up and review.

83
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,360
The basic characteristics of news are truth, freshness, and openness.

84
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,960
Truth is the lifeblood of news,

85
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:57,480
requiring news to reflect real and objective facts.

86
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,320
Freshness is why news exists.

87
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,720
Yang Qian.

88
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,520
Why hasn't Zixi been coming to class lately?

89
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,280
She's studying for a makeup exam.

90
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,160
What's wrong?

91
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,360
Does she still need to study?

92
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,640
Doesn't she already have the exam answers?

93
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:20,120
Oh.

94
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,360
So it was you.

95
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:24,160
What? You don't want her to know?

96
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:26,880
Not really.

97
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,080
Where is she now?

98
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,640
I wouldn't know about that.

99
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,520
Tell her directly.

100
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,240
Tell her indirectly.

101
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:36,960
Don't tell her.

102
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:40,060
You've been counting these three drafts all night.

103
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,800
It's all because of you.

104
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:43,880
Yes.

105
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,880
Then what can I do?

106
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:48,010
I am willing to make up for my mistakes.

107
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:53,480
What can you do?

108
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,560
Ah.

109
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:10,720
Why are there still security guards patrolling?

110
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,600
Your yelling brought them here.

111
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,120
It's because you didn't wake me up.

112
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,160
I overslept.

113
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:16,680
Who is it?

114
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:17,880
Who's there?

115
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,420
I heard your voice.

116
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,480
Come out now.

117
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,760
Follow me.

118
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:40,120
What was that? Who is it?

119
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,280
Let's go.

120
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,500
Didn't the security guard leave?

121
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:22,120
Old Chen, I've checked the broadcasting room.

122
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,120
No one is there.

123
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,520
What's wrong?

124
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,159
Campus secret.

125
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,720
This is English written backwards.

126
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,600
Oh.

127
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,600
The senior from your broadcasting station

128
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,160
is quite romantic.

129
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,240
Writing it in such a hidden place,

130
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,880
must have been hard for him.

131
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,080
Yeah.

132
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:32,010
The security guard should be gone.

133
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,200
It's so late.

134
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:42,039
I wonder if we can still get into the dorm.

135
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:44,880
We've fallen behind a lot.

136
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:51,260
Won't lighting this lamp get us discovered?

137
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:55,240
I tried it last night.

138
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,280
The brightness is limited.

139
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,720
It can't be seen from outside.

140
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,560
Last night?

141
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,530
Did you think I didn't need to prepare review materials?

142
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,760
Did he start preparing last night?

143
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,610
Why are you spacing out?

144
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,330
We haven't started on the key points here.

145
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,280
So much?

146
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:12,840
You slept all afternoon.

147
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,320
We should make up for it.

148
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,800
The authenticity of news is

149
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,880
that every specific fact

150
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,080
in the news report.

151
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:25,080
Must conform to objective reality.

152
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,320
Brother.

153
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,840
Can I refuse?

154
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,720
A gentleman's word

155
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,840
is hard to take back.

156
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,760
Wake up.

157
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:40,960
Don't study for days

158
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,840
and end up missing the exam.

159
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,640
A small accident.

160
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:05,480
What small accident?

161
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,800
They even brought a cheer squad for a makeup exam.

162
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,120
Enemies really do cross paths.

163
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:23,680
Go, Yin Zixi!

164
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:25,840
Zixi.

165
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,980
Actually, those exam answers

166
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,680
were sent by me.

167
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:33,000
I did this

168
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,200
actually because...

169
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:34,680
Boss.

170
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,690
For something this embarrassing,

171
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,040
it'll cost extra.

172
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,360
Isn't it all because of you?

173
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,360
You sent the answers but didn't even leave your name.

174
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:48,160
If we don't do something now,

175
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:49,940
wouldn't it be a waste?

176
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,960
Yes.

177
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,960
Hello, everyone.

178
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,600
It's been a while since the last broadcast.

179
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,800
I've recently hit a low point in my life.

180
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,480
I can't see any hope here.

181
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,480
It makes me feel powerless and exhausted.

182
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,400
An unexpected encounter

183
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,400
has made me waver.

184
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:22,040
It feels like returning to the days when I fought hard.

185
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,080
I started to reflect.

186
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,760
Am I really powerless?

187
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,880
Did I give up too quickly?

188
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,360
Is there really nothing I can do?

189
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,440
Even if I am powerless,

190
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,680
I will give it my all.

191
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:40,640
I also want to say a few words to the students taking the exam today.

192
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:43,040
Youth is about running hard,

193
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,280
and then falling gracefully.

194
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:48,320
But being young gives us the courage to stand back up.

195
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:51,120
Enjoy falling and getting back up again.

196
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:53,960
Finally, I wish the students taking the exam today

197
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:56,120
good luck.

198
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:10,320
Associate Casting Director Xi Chongjing

199
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:12,200
Props Assistant Li Kunxiao

200
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:14,160
Unit Vehicle Yi Mingle

201
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,040
Yitong
